documentation_summary: Akshare is a Python library designed to provide an elegant and simple interface for financial data retrieval, catering to the needs of human users. It requires Python 3.8 or higher and is compatible with various Python versions up to 3.12. The library is licensed under the MIT License and is maintained by the AKFamily. It supports a wide range of financial data types, including stocks, options, futures, funds, bonds, and indices, among others. Akshare emphasizes ease of use, extensibility, and the power of the Python ecosystem. It offers detailed documentation and installation instructions, including Docker support for containerized environments. The project encourages contributions from the community, including bug reports, interface requests, documentation improvements, and test case additions. Akshare is open-source and provides data solely for academic research, without any investment advice.
